# Cognito user seeding (optional).
#
# Copy this file to `users.yaml` in the same directory and list the people who
# should get accounts. On `terraform apply` (with auth_enabled = true) each user
# is created in the standard invite flow: Cognito generates a temporary password
# and emails an invite; the user sets their own password (min 12 chars, mixed
# case + number + symbol) on first login. Terraform never holds a password.
#
# This file is declarative:
#   - add an entry + re-apply        -> account created, invite emailed
#   - remove an entry + re-apply     -> account deleted
#   - already-present users          -> left untouched
#
# Notes:
#   - Only used when auth_enabled = true. When federating an external IdP
#     (JumpCloud/Okta/...) for SSO, leave this empty — users come from the IdP.
#   - Cognito's default email sender is capped at ~50/day and sends from a
#     generic address. For a real rollout wire SES into the pool.
#
# `users.yaml` is gitignored so your real roster isn't committed.

- email: alice@example.com
  name: Alice Example          # optional; maps to the Cognito `name` attribute

- email: bob@example.com        # name is optional

- email: carol@example.com
